HEADWORD: hadrosaur
<hw>hadrosaur</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any member of the genus
<gen>Hadrosaurus</gen> or family <fam>Hadrosauridae</fam>, an extinct
family of heavy bipedal partly aquatic dinosaurs with duck-billed skull
and webbed feet; of the Upper Cretaceous in North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hadrosaurus.</syn>⟦br⟧
